Document: TouchScreenButton
Path: godot/classes/class_touchscreenbutton.rst
Summary: A button that can be pressed by touching the screen.

Inherits: TextureButton < Button < BaseButton < Control < CanvasItem < Node < Object

A button that can be pressed by touching the screen. It's a specialized version of TextureButton that handles touch input.

This node is useful for creating on-screen buttons for games or applications that will be played on touch devices. It provides visual feedback when touched and can trigger actions when pressed.

Key Rule: TouchScreenButton is designed specifically for touch input and may not behave as expected with mouse or keyboard input.
