Document: TouchScreenButton
Path: godot/classes/class_touchscreenbutton.rst
Summary: Describes the TouchScreenButton node, its purpose for on-screen touch controls, inheritance, and differences from Control and Button nodes.
TouchScreenButton allows you to create on-screen buttons for touch devices. It's intended for gameplay use, such as a unit you have to touch to move. Unlike Button, TouchScreenButton supports multitouch out of the box. Several TouchScreenButtons can be pressed at the same time with touch input.

This node inherits from Node2D. Unlike with Control nodes, you cannot set anchors on it. If you want to create menus or user interfaces, you may want to use Button nodes instead. To make button nodes react to touch events, you can enable ProjectSettings.input_devices/pointing/emulate_mouse_from_touch in the Project Settings.

You can configure TouchScreenButton to be visible only on touch devices, helping you develop your game both for desktop and mobile devices.
---CHUNK---
Document: TouchScreenButton
Path: godot/classes/class_touchscreenbutton.rst
Summary: Defines the properties available for the TouchScreenButton class, including action, bitmask, passby_press, shape, shape_centered, shape_visible, textures, and visibility mode.

Properties
* action (String): The action name that will be emitted when the button is pressed. Default: ""
* bitmask (BitMap): A bitmask to filter which touch IDs can interact with this button.
* passby_press (bool): If true, the touch event will be passed through to the underlying controls when the button is pressed. Default: false
* shape (Shape2D): The shape used for collision detection.
* shape_centered (bool): If true, the shape will be centered within the button's area. Default: true
* shape_visible (bool): If true, the shape will be visible. Default: true
* texture_normal (Texture2D): The texture to display when the button is in its normal state.
* texture_pressed (Texture2D): The texture to display when the button is pressed.
* visibility_mode (VisibilityMode): Controls when the button is visible. Default: 0
---CHUNK---
Document: TouchScreenButton
Path: godot/classes/class_touchscreenbutton.rst
Summary: This section describes the methods, signals, and enumerations available for the TouchScreenButton class in Godot.
Method: is_pressed() → bool
This method checks if the button is currently being pressed.

Signals
pressed(): Emitted when the button is pressed (down).
released(): Emitted when the button is released (up).

Enumerations
enum VisibilityMode:
VISIBILITY_ALWAYS = 0: Always visible.
VISIBILITY_TOUCHSCREEN_ONLY = 1: Visible on touch screens only.
