Document: TouchScreenButton
Path: godot/classes/class_touchscreenbutton.rst
Summary: Describes the properties and member variables of the TouchScreenButton class in Godot Engine.

Property: action (String)
Description: The button's action. Actions can be handled with InputEventAction.
Setters/Getters: set_action(value: String), get_action() → String

Property: bitmask (BitMap)
Description: The button's bitmask.
Setters/Getters: set_bitmask(value: BitMap), get_bitmask() → BitMap

Property: passby_press (bool)
Default: false
Description: If true, the pressed and released signals are emitted whenever a pressed finger goes in and out of the button, even if the pressure started outside the active area of the button.
Note: This is a "pass-by" (not "bypass") press mode.
Setters/Getters: set_passby_press(value: bool), is_passby_press_enabled() → bool

Property: shape (Shape2D)
Description: The button's shape.
Setters/Getters: set_shape(value: Shape2D), get_shape() → Shape2D

Property: shape_centered (bool)
Default: true
Description: If true, the button's shape is centered in the provided texture. If no texture is used, this property has no effect.
Setters/Getters: set_shape_centered(value: bool), is_shape_centered() → bool

Property: shape_visible (bool)
Default: true
Description: If true, the button's shape is visible in the editor.
Setters/Getters: set_shape_visible(value: bool), is_shape_visible() → bool

Property: texture_normal (Texture2D)
Description: The button's texture for the normal state.
Setters/Getters: set_texture_normal(value: Texture2D), get_texture_normal() → Texture2D

Property: texture_pressed (Texture2D)
Description: The button's texture for the pressed state.
Setters/Getters: set_texture_pressed(value: Texture2D), get_texture_pressed() → Texture2D

Property: visibility_mode (VisibilityMode)
Default: 0
Description: The button's visibility mode.
Setters/Getters: set_visibility_mode(value: VisibilityMode), get_visibility_mode() → VisibilityMode
---CHUNK---
